<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><b><font style="font-size: 24px;">Install the x11vnc Server</font></b></div><div><br /></div><div>=&gt;<b> cd</b> <font color="#941100">/usr/ports/net/x11vnc</font></div><div>=&gt; <font color="#ff2f92">sudo</font> <b>make install clean</b></div><div><font color="#929292"># Create a password which will be used to login</font></div><div>=&gt; <b>x11vnc</b> <font color="#0096ff">-storepassword</font></div><div><font color="#929292"># The above command will create the password and stores in</font></div><div><font color="#929292"># the $USER/.vnc/password file</font></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># To start the server:</font></div><div>=&gt; <b>x11vnc</b> <font color="#0096ff">-rfbauthb</font> <font color="#941100">/home/khasanov/.vnc/</font><font color="#009193">passwd</font> <font color="#0096ff">-forever</font> <font color="#0096ff">-display</font> <font color="#009051"><b>:0</b></font></div><div># Note: There is the space between “<font color="#0096ff">display</font>” and “<b><font color="#009051">:0</font></b>”  (‘0’ means first display)</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><b><font style="font-size: 24px;">Using the VNC Server from the client side</font></b></div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># I am using the Mac OS X on iMac</font></div><div><b>Go</b> -&gt;<b> Connect To Server..</b> </div><div><br /></div><div> <en-media hash="ff1be83561857d399fb28962410e96e3" type="image/png" /></div><div><br /></div><div>Then you need to enter the password you’ve created for the x11nvc.</div></en-note>